# OWASP Juice Shop — Project Memory (post-/init example)

> **Authorized training only.** Juice Shop is an intentionally vulnerable app. Do not repurpose findings against systems you don't own.

## Stack
- Node 20.x / 22.x / 24.x, TypeScript (Juice Shop v19+ dropped Node 18)
- Express (backend), Angular (frontend)
- SQLite via Sequelize
- Frisby + Cypress

## Commands
- `npm install`, `npm start`, `npm test`, `npm run frisby`, `npm run cypress:open`, `npm run lint`

## Key directories
- `routes/`, `lib/` — backend route handlers and helpers
- `models/` — Sequelize models
- `data/static/*.yml` — challenge registry + seed data
- `frontend/src/app/` — Angular app
- `test/` — Frisby specs

## Intentional gotchas (don't "fix" without a learner-patch exercise)
- Hardcoded weak JWT secret
- Sample `.env` with dummy values
- Known-bad SQL patterns in login / search
- Score-board at `/#/score-board` tracks which challenges you've solved

## Don't touch
- `node_modules/`, `build/`, `dist/`, `frontend/dist/`
- `data/juicer.sqlite` (regenerated at startup)
